                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331017-107-defend1041 t18331017-107-deflabel587"></join> - I had the greatest confidence in him - on the 23rd of September I put £1 worth of silver into a drawer, in my desk; there was no one in the shop but the prisoner and I; in the evening I went to look and half-a-crown was gone - on the 25th I marked £1 worth of silver; four half-crowns, nine shillings, and two sixpences, and 5s. in copper - I went to it again, and a half-crown was gone; I had left the drawer locked, and found it so - I sent for an officer, who searched the prisoner, and found the half-crown in his waistcoat pocket; and 5d. in copper, in his jacket pocket; I counted the copper in the drawer, and 5d. was gone.</p>

